============================================================
WHY EVERY SX PAIR CHANGES SIGMA
============================================================
Algebraic formula for delta_sigma:
  For SX pair (s,x): delta_sigma = -sum_{w in S, w!=s} sign(s->w)*sign(x->w)
  where sign(u->v) = A[u][v] - A[v][u] in {-1,+1}

Formula verified: 1476/1476

Key insight: sum of 3 terms in {-1,+1} is ALWAYS odd, so NEVER 0.
Therefore delta_sigma(s,x) is ALWAYS nonzero for SX pairs.
This PROVES that sigma changes for ALL |S|*(n-|S|) = 4*(n-4) SX pairs.

delta_sigma values for SX pairs:
  delta_sigma distribution for SX pairs: {-1: 738, 1: 738}
  Always +/-1? True

Done.
